(79, 1, '2025-09-28 14:19:37', '2025-09-28 14:19:37', '<p dir=\"auto\">The iPhone 17 Pro, announced on September 9, 2025, at Apple\'s \"Awe Dropping\" event in Cupertino, California, alongside the iPhone 17, iPhone Air, and iPhone 17 Pro Max, marks a significant evolution in Apple\'s Pro lineup. It introduces a redesigned aluminum unibody chassis for better thermal management, the A19 Pro chip for peak performance, and a triple 48MP camera system with 8x optical zoomthe longest ever on an iPhone. Running iOS 26 with enhanced Apple Intelligence features like improved Live Translation and Visual Intelligence in screenshots, it\'s optimized for creators, gamers, and pros. Pre-orders started September 12, with global availability from September 19, 2025. Demand has exceeded expectations, prompting Apple to ramp up production, and it\'s already shipping widely as of late September. Priced starting at $1,099 (a $100 hike from the iPhone 16 Pro due to added features and inflation pressures), it\'s available in Cosmic Orange, Deep Blue, and Silver. Recent X posts buzz about restocks on Amazon and Verizon, with users raving about battery life but noting minor iOS 26 bugs like Wi-Fi drops.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"auto\">This compact flagship (6.3-inch display) targets users wanting Pro power without the Pro Max\'s bulk, excelling in video production with ProRes RAW and Apple Log 2 support. iFixit scores its repairability at 7/10, improved by the modular design but challenged by the new camera bump. On X, early adopters highlight the \"record autonomy\" in Europe, where it\'s priced around 1,199, calling it a \"bon plan\" for its value despite the cost.</p>', 'Apple iPhone 17 Pro', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'hi-fi-headphones', '', '', '2025-09-29 19:04:22', '2025-09-29 19:04:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/index.php/product/hi-fi-headphones/', 0, 'product', '', 0),
