(83, 1, '2025-09-28 14:19:38', '2025-09-28 14:19:38', '<p dir=\"auto\">The Apple AirPods Pro 3, unveiled on September 9, 2025, at Apple\'s \"Awe Dropping\" event alongside the iPhone 17 series, represent the most significant update to Apple\'s premium wireless earbuds since the AirPods Pro 2 in 2022. Priced at a competitive $249 (unchanged from the Pro 2), they focus on superior audio immersion, health integration, and AI-driven features like real-time Live Translation. Pre-orders began immediately after the event, with shipping starting September 19, 2025making them widely available now, just weeks into their lifecycle. Apple claims these are the \"best-fitting AirPods ever,\" based on over 10,000 ear scans and 100,000+ hours of user research, resulting in a refined in-ear design that\'s 20% smaller internally for better stability during activities.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"auto\">These earbuds excel in noise cancellation (up to 2x better than Pro 2) and battery life, positioning them as a top choice for commuters, athletes, and audiophiles. They\'re fully integrated with iOS 26\'s Apple Intelligence, enhancing ecosystem features like workout tracking via the Fitness app. A 2026 variant with infrared cameras for gesture control and Vision Pro spatial audio is rumored, but the current model stands alone as the flagship. Recent X chatter highlights praise for sound quality over rivals like Galaxy Buds 3 Pro, though some users report ear discomfort or iOS compatibility quirks.</p>', 'Apple AirPods Pro 3', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'black-and-white', '', '', '2025-09-29 19:03:11', '2025-09-29 19:03:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/index.php/product/black-and-white/', 0, 'product', '', 0),
