(85, 1, '2025-09-28 14:19:39', '2025-09-28 14:19:39', '<p dir=\"auto\">The Xiaomi 17 series, launched on September 25, 2025, in China, represents Xiaomi\'s flagship lineup for the year, skipping the \"16\" numbering to align with a \"cross-generational upgrade\" strategy. It directly competes with the iPhone 17 series, emphasizing superior battery life, performance, and imaging without price hikes for the base model. The series includes three models: <strong>Xiaomi 17</strong> (compact all-rounder), <strong>Xiaomi 17 Pro</strong> (premium compact with dual screens), and <strong>Xiaomi 17 Pro Max</strong> (large-screen powerhouse). All run <strong>HyperOS 3</strong> based on <strong>Android 16</strong>, feature Leica-tuned cameras, and are powered by the world\'s first <strong>Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5</strong> chipset (3nm process, up to 4.6GHz CPU clock, 20% better performance and efficiency over predecessors).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"auto\">These phones are currently available only in China, with pre-orders starting immediately after launch and full sales on September 27, 2025. They broke sales records within 5 minutes of going on sale, surpassing 2025\'s domestic flagship benchmarks. A global launch (including Europe and India) is expected in early 2026, possibly around MWC in February, with the base Xiaomi 17 and Pro Max most likely to appear outside China. An <strong>Xiaomi 17 Ultra</strong> variant is rumored for a global release with enhanced satellite connectivity and camera hardware, potentially launching earlier than usual.</p>', 'Xiaomi 17 Pro', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'leather-clad-leisure-chair', '', '', '2025-09-29 19:00:55', '2025-09-29 19:00:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/index.php/product/leather-clad-leisure-chair/', 0, 'product', '', 0),
