(87, 1, '2025-09-28 14:19:39', '2025-09-28 14:19:39', '<p dir=\"auto\">The Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra, released earlier this year, is the flagship powerhouse of the Galaxy S25 series, succeeding the S24 Ultra with refinements in AI, performance, and design. Announced on January 22, 2025, at Samsung\'s Galaxy Unpacked event in San Jose, California, it hit global markets on February 7, 2025. It emphasizes \"human-like\" Galaxy AI enhancements, such as cross-app actions (e.g., summarizing YouTube videos or sharing info seamlessly via natural language), Now Brief (personalized daily insights like weather or health scores), and Circle to Search. Powered by the Snapdragon 8 Elite (custom \"for Galaxy\" variant with 40% better image processing and ray-tracing for gaming), it runs Android 15 with One UI 7 out of the box, promising 7 years of OS updates.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"auto\">This phone targets power users, photographers, and productivity pros, with a titanium frame, integrated S Pen (Bluetooth removed to slim it down), and a focus on sustained performance via a 40% larger vapor chamber. It\'s manufactured in Vietnam, India, and Egypt for global distribution. As of September 29, 2025, it\'s widely available, with recent user buzz on X praising its multitasking and camera over iPhones, though some critique the 3x telephoto sensor\'s small size (~1/3.6-inch, comparable to older iPhone cams).</p>', 'Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'vintage-typewriter', '', '', '2025-09-29 19:02:23', '2025-09-29 19:02:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/index.php/product/vintage-typewriter/', 0, 'product', '', 0),
